@zjffdu 
I solved this problem and it is not actually a Zeppelin issue.
The main problem is that the contentType in the livy service http header has no charset option.

Livy file location:
`Vim server/src/main/scala/org/apache/livy/server/SessionServlet.scala +67`

```
before() {

         // contentType = "application/json"

         contentType = "application/json;charset=UTF-8"

  }
```

rebuild livy server

@zjffdu Great idea on paragraph-level properties! There are so many possible uses for this feature like ones you explained below.

For interpolation I think there should be a way to do it globally too, to match Jupyter's behavior. And it could be also optionally enabled at paragraph level like you're describing. Not sure I understood on overhead though - since it will be only applied to code in the paragraphs.

@sanjaydasgupta 
> I am thinking if we need (2) at all, since (1) alone is enough for allowing users to start using the new feature in a safe and controlled way.

I agree, thank you.

@zjffdu, what @sanjaydasgupta is saying allows to switch this feature off at global level, so we can maintain compatibility with previous version, and only switch interpolation when users choose to enable it. It looks like a good idea to me. We could add enabling this at paragraph-level as part of another PR later, when this new facility to have paragraph-level properties will be available. What do you guys think?

@zjffdu, @felixcheung would be exciting to have this feature be part of the 0.8.0 release.
Since there is a way to maintain backward compatibility, it seems to be a low hanging fruit 
as it's a great improvement in Zeppelin functionality. Thanks @sanjaydasgupta and everyone!

